{{Episode list
| EpisodeNumber   = 1
| Title           = Pilot
| DirectedBy      = [[Adam Davidson (director)|Adam Davidson]]
| WrittenBy       = ''Teleplay & television story by'':<br />[[Robert Kirkman]] & [[Dave Erickson]]
| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|8|23}}
| Viewers         = 10.13<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/08/25/sunday-cable-ratings-fear-the-walking-dead-tops-night-talking-dead-naked-afraid-rick-morty-more/452479/ |title=Sunday Cable Ratings: 'Fear the Walking Dead' Tops Night + 'Talking Dead', 'Naked & Afraid', 'Rick & Morty', & More |work=TV by the Numbers |first=Amanda |last=Kondolojy |date=August 25, 2015 |accessdate=August 25, 2015}}</ref>
| ShortSummary    = Nick awakens in a heroin den in an abandoned church and finds his friend Gloria eating a bloodied corpse. He flees, but is hit by a car and hospitalized. Nick's doctor tells Madison and Travis that Nick's claims about the incident are heroin hallucinations. With Liza's aid, Travis tries to mend things with rebellious Christopher.  Travis visits the church and believes Nick's story. Alicia becomes more worried about Nick's chemical dependency. At school, Madison confiscates Tobias' knife. He warns her about a mysterious epidemic. School closes early the next day after news video of a violent man who seems unaffected by police bullet.  Travis and Madison were caught in that traffic-jammed scene the night before. Nick escapes from the hospital and meets with Calvin, hoping to learn if the drugs Calvin sold him were bad and caused him to hallucinate. Calvin drives Nick to the riverfront, where Calvin plans to kill him in order to prevent him from exposing him as a drug dealer. Calvin is shot and killed in a struggle with Nick. After Travis and Madison arrive, the zombified Calvin attacks them. Nick runs over Calvin repeatedly with Travis' truck, and the three watch in disbelief as the mutilated Calvin keeps getting back up and turns to face them.
| LineColor       = 78000D
}}
{{Episode list
| EpisodeNumber   = 2
| Title           = So Close, Yet So Far
| DirectedBy      = Adam Davidson
| WrittenBy       = Marco Ramirez
| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|8|30}}
| Viewers         = 8.18<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/09/01/sunday-cable-ratings-fear-the-walking-dead-wins-night-mtv-video-music-awards-rick-morty-the-last-ship-falling-skies-ray-donovan-more/456023/|title=Sunday Cable Ratings: 'Fear The Walking Dead' Wins Night, 'MTV Video Music Awards', 'Rick & Morty', 'The Last Ship', 'Falling Skies', 'Ray Donovan' & More|last=Bibel|first=Sara|date=September 1, 2015|work=TV by the Numbers|accessdate=September 1, 2015}}</ref>
| ShortSummary    = After the run-in with zombified Calvin, Nick, Madison, and Travis decide to flee to the desert and try to persuade Alicia, Liza, and Chris to go along. Alicia finds Matt ill in his disheveled house. Travis arrives and sees a bite on Matt.  Matt convinces Alicia to leave. The group returns home to gather supplies. Nick suffers heroin withdrawal, so Madison drives to her school to get drugs that were confiscated from other students. There she encounters Tobias scavenging food. A zombified Artie tries to bite Tobias, so Madison kills Artie and drives Tobias home. Chris’ bus is trapped in a traffic jam caused by a fatal zombie shooting. He films the event and joins in a protest against the fatal police shootings.  Travis and Liza meet up with him at the protest. A riot erupts after police shoot and kill another zombie, but the three Manawas find refuge with the Salazars in their gated barbershop-home. Travis tells Madison to take the kids to the desert without him; he will catch up. Alicia witnesses their undead neighbor Mr. Dawson attacking Mrs. Cruz across the street.  Madison doesn't let her intervene. The group inside the barbershop is trapped while the riot outside intensifies.
| LineColor       = 78000D
}}
{{Episode list
| EpisodeNumber   = 3
| Title           = The Dog
| DirectedBy      = Adam Davidson
| WrittenBy       = [[Jack LoGiudice]]
| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|9|13}}
| Viewers         = 7.19<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/09/15/sunday-cable-ratings-fear-the-walking-dead-tops-night-rick-morty-the-strain-nfl-countdown-more/466414/|title=Sunday Cable Ratings: 'Fear The Walking Dead' Tops Night + 'Rick & Morty', 'The Strain', NFL Countdown & More|last=Dixon|first=Dani|work=TV by the Numbers|date=September 15, 2015|accessdate=September 15, 2015}}</ref>
| ShortSummary    =  The riot continues to rage outside.  The barbershop occupants take advantage of a fire the mob sets to flee through an adjacent store. The group reaches Travis' truck and escapes, but not before Griselda is injured by a collapsing scaffold. They drive her to a hospital, but it is blocked by police due to zombie activity. The group drives to Madison's house.  An undead Mr. Dawson hears the dog Nick let inside barking and attempts to enter the home.  Nick, Madison, and Alicia flee zombie Dawson.  Nick leads Madison and Alicia to the Trans' house, where they take a shotgun but leave without shells for it. Alicia returns to get them and is runs away from her undead neighbor Susan. Travis' group reaches Madison's house. Daniel fatally shoots Dawson and stops his attack on Travis. All three families decide to stay the night and evacuate in the morning. Nurse Liza tends to Griselda's injured foot and says she will die without professional medical assistance. Ofelia tells Daniel they should flee with Travis.  Daniel insists his family can survive alone and will join his cousin later. The next morning, as the Clarks and Manawas try to drive away, the National Guard arrives and quarantines the block. While Travis says, "It's going to get better,” Daniel laments that it’s, "too late," as he watches a guardsman mark the neighboring house.
| LineColor       = 78000D
}}
{{Episode list
| EpisodeNumber   = 4
| Title           = Not Fade Away
| DirectedBy      = [[Kari Skogland]]
| WrittenBy       = Meaghan Oppenheimer
| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|9|20}}
| Viewers         = 6.62<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/09/22/sunday-cable-ratings-fear-the-walking-dead-tops-night-nfl-countdown-rick-morty-basketball-wives-the-strain-more/469914/|title=Sunday Cable Ratings: 'Fear The Walking Dead' Tops Night + 'NFL Countdown', 'Rick & Morty', 'Basketball Wives', 'The Strain' & More|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda|work=TV by the Numbers|date=September 22, 2015|accessdate=September 22, 2015}}</ref>
| ShortSummary    = Days have passed since the National Guard quarantined the neighborhood into a Safe Zone (aka [[Demilitarized zone|DZ]]).  The residents try to resume normal lives. Tensions build under military rules. Madison is stressed by extra work caused by her home's overcrowding and Travis' new role as civilian liaison. Chris shows a video to Travis and Madison of a signal light from the Dead Zone. Travis talks Doug into getting mental help. Liza gives medical treatment to neighbors. Nick steals morphine from Hector, a cancer patient, via his [[IV drip]]. Ofelia kisses Adams, who was unable to get Griselda's medicine. Madison exchanges signals with the flashing light in the Dead Zone. She sneaks outside the fence to investigate and finds evidence that the guardsmen killed civilians, including the uninfected. Travis learns that Doug was hospitalized over mental issues. Dr. Exner decides Liza is not a nurse. Daniel warns Madison of his El Salvador experience, when the sick were arrested and their families told they were being hospitalized for treatment when they were actually being murdered. Soldiers take Griselda and Nick to a hospital over the objections of Nick's family. Liza agrees to go along and assist the medical team despite her desire not to leave her son. Travis retreats to the roof and sees the signal from the Dead Zone. Seconds later, he sees and hears gunfire, followed by darkness.
| LineColor       = 78000D
}}
{{Episode list
| EpisodeNumber   = 5
| Title           = Cobalt
| DirectedBy      = Kari Skogland
| WrittenBy       = David Wiener
| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|9|27}}
| Viewers         = 6.66<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/09/29/sunday-cable-ratings-fear-the-walking-dead-tops-night-rick-morty-basketball-wives-the-strain-more/473460/|title=Sunday Cable Ratings: 'Fear The Walking Dead' Tops Night + 'Rick & Morty', 'Basketball Wives', 'The Strain' & More|last=Dixon|first=Dani|work=TV by the Numbers|date=September 29, 2015|accessdate=September 29, 2015}}</ref>
| ShortSummary    = In a military cell, Strand torments Doug, who breaks down and is removed. Strand bribes a guardsman to save Nick, who is feverish from heroin withdrawal. (The soldiers and medical crew are observing their prisoners for symptoms and taking their temperature regularly). Liza helps Dr. Exner with patients at the hospital. Ofelia hurls debris at the Safe Zone gate, enraged because the soldiers took Griselda. Adams calms her and takes her home. Chris is devastated that Liza left to volunteer at the hospital.  Travis promises to bring her back. Madison discovers Adams in the Trans' basement, where he is being tortured and questioned by Daniel. Alicia and Chris get drunk in and vandalize a wealthy family's abandoned home. Strand recruits Nick for an escape plot. Travis convinces Moyers' squad to take him to the hospital to check on his friends. En route, Moyers encourages Travis to shoot a zombie, but he still views the undead as human beings and can't bring himself to do it. The soldiers stop to assist another squad in a zombie-infested building.  Most of the soldiers, including Moyers, are killed or bitten. The few survivors flee and drop off Travis near the Safe Zone. Travis learns that Daniel tortured Adams into revealing what "Cobalt" means.  All civilians will be killed the next day, and the guardsmen will evacuate the city. Griselda dies of septic shock at the hospital. Liza shoots her in the brain to prevent reanimation. Daniel visits a nearby sports arena to verify Adams' story that it was sealed with 2,000 civilians, some of them still alive, inside.
| LineColor       = 78000D
}}
{{Episode list
| EpisodeNumber   = 6
| Title           = The Good Man
| DirectedBy      = [[Stefan Schwartz]]
| WrittenBy       = Robert Kirkman & Dave Erickson
| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|10|4}}
| Viewers         = 6.86<ref name="1.06">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/10/06/sunday-cable-ratings-fear-the-walking-dead-finale-leads-night-strain-finale-rick-morty-kardashians/476968/|title=Sunday cable ratings: 'Fear the Walking Dead' finale leads night, plus 'The Strain' finale, 'Rick & Morty,' 'Kardashians'|last=Porter|first=Rick|work=TV by the Numbers|date=October 6, 2015|accessdate=October 6, 2015}}</ref>
| ShortSummary    =  The group prepares to evacuate the neighborhood and rescue Liza, Griselda and Nick before the soldiers initiate Cobalt.  Adams begs Daniel not to kill him, saying he can guide them to the hospital and out of it.  Adams privately warns Travis that Daniel will kill Adams when he is no longer useful and Travis decides to release him. The group goes to National Guard headquarters. Daniel distracts the guards by leading a horde of walkers from the arena to the headquarters perimeter. Travis, Madison, Daniel, and Ofelia get inside the base, leaving Alicia and Chris with their vehicles. Inside the base, Strand and Nick launch their escape plan.  Strand callously leaves other detainees locked in their cells. Meanwhile, the walkers breach the perimeter defenses and swarm the base. Travis' group comes across the holding cells and frees the detainees before reuniting with Nick, Liza, and Strand. They try to escape through the medical ward, where they find Dr. Exner has euthanized all the patients. Dr. Exner tells them about an escape route before presumably committing suicide. Before they can escape, the group encounters Adams, who shoots Ofelia in the arm. Enraged, Travis brutally beats Adams and leaves him for dead. Strand leads the group to his oceanside mansion, where he tells Nick he will escape on his yacht, the ''Abigail'', which is anchored just off the coast. On the beach, Liza tells Madison she was bitten during the escape. Liza pleads with Madison and Travis to euthanize her before she turns. Travis promises to protect Chris before shooting Liza.  Madison tries to comfort the grieving Travis.
| LineColor       = 78000D
}}
}}
